rong>TACTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>During Combat </strong>Tarrin uses her spells to hold or stun enemies, allowing her scouts to make sneak attacks on her foes. If she sees a chance to flank, she combines Channel Smite with a sneak attack.</p><p><strong>Morale </strong>Tarrin fights to the death in the shrine. If encountered elsewhere, she flees if reduced to 10 hit points or fewer.</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str </strong>8, <strong>Dex </strong>14, <strong>Con </strong>14, <strong>Int </strong> 10, <strong>Wis </strong>17, <strong>Cha </strong>12</p><p><strong>Base Atk </strong>+3; <strong>CMB </strong>+2; <strong>CMD </strong>14</p><p><strong>Feats </strong>Channel Smite, Combat Casting, Improved Initiative, Spell Focus (enchantment), Weapon Finesse</p><p><strong>Skills </strong>Acrobatics +5, Bluff +9, Diplomacy +5, Disable Device +5, Escape Artist +5, Knowledge (religion) +8, Perception +11, Spellcraft +8, Stealth +7</p><p><strong>Languages </strong>Common</p><p><strong>SQ </strong>rogue talents (finesse rogue), trapfinding +1</p><p><strong>Combat Gear </strong><i>potion of invisibility</i>; <strong>Other Gear </strong><i>+1 chain shirt</i>, <i>+1 rapier</i>, light crossbow, holy symbol</p></div></section>","img":"systems/pf1/icons/races/creature-types/humanoid.jpg","_id":"iJbDoN5uBQKhQq13"}
